      • domain

        public String domain
        The domain that the resulting terms must be in, or null for any domain.

      • entryId

        public String entryId
        The entry ID to look for. This matches all terms that are associated with an entry, including the head term. Use null to not filter by entry ID.

      • customCriteria

        public List<String> customCriteria
        Custom search criteria in form of a list of strings. Each string must be a "field=value" criterion. The first occurrence of the equality sign '=' is taken as the separator between field and value name. You can match term and entry fields. The same field names must be used as they appear in the requested output of the findTerms method. For example, query "term/status" when asking for ACTIF and "adminStatus" when asking for OLIF. Category values are tried to be interpreted as a category. Text values are matched exactly. For date fields, you may (and need to) use a range relation '<' and '>' preceding the date as it appears in the output. For example, use the value "term/creation-date-time=<2012-05-10T11:41:00" to find all terms that are older than May 10, 2012, 11:41:00. For technical reasons, you cannot query on fields that cannot be used in a filter on the dashboard. Currently, the affected fields are (ACTIF notation): term/id term/uuid term/frequency

      • format

        public String format
        The desired output format.

      • withSchema

        public boolean withSchema
        Set to true to also get the schema in the response (only considered for ACTIF).
